{"title":"LXV [Once, I knew a fine song]","author":{"name":"Stephen Crane"},"publishDate":"2016-05-04","lines":[{"line":"Once, I knew a fine song,","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"—It is true, believe me,—","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"It was all of birds,","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"And I held them in a basket;","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"When I opened the wicket,","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"Heavens! They all flew away.","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"I cried, “Come back, little thoughts!”","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"But they only laughed.","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"They flew on","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"Until they were as sand","stanza":1,"number":10},{"line":"Thrown between me and the sky.","stanza":1,"number":11}]}